                <div class="project-description">
                    <p>
                        <strong>Book Tracker</strong> is a full-stack CRUD web application that allows users to track books they’ve read, including ratings, reviews, and cover images. It was built using Node.js, Express.js, and EJS.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Users can:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Add and store book details including author, title, rating, review, and read date</li>
                        <li>Edit and delete entries</li>
                        <li>Search and sort books efficiently</li>
                        <li>View book cover images fetched using Axios and public APIs</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        I have used PostgreSQL in this project to store and manage book data such as titles, authors, ratings, reviews, and read dates in a structured relational database.
                        The app uses Axios for backend API calls and dynamically renders pages with EJS templates.
                    </p>
